# Snow Leopard Codex (MySQL) â€” Build-from-Scratch Relational Database

A small portfolio database project built from scratch in MySQL to practice:
- schema design and normalization
- primary keys, foreign keys, and constraints
- many-to-many relationships via a junction table
- querying across multiple tables
- backup + restore workflow using `mysqldump`

## Schema Overview

**Tables**
- `realms` â€” environment metadata (magic density, climate)
- `creatures` â€” creatures and their home realm
- `abilities` â€” ability catalog with elemental types
- `creature_abilities` â€” junction table linking creatures to abilities + acquired level

**Relationships**
- `creatures.realm_id â†’ realms.realm_id` (many creatures to one realm)
- `creature_abilities.creature_id â†’ creatures.creature_id`
- `creature_abilities.ability_id â†’ abilities.ability_id`  
(many-to-many between creatures and abilities)

## Setup (MySQL)

```sql
CREATE DATABASE snow_leopard_codex;
USE snow_leopard_codex;

---TABLES---
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+
| creature_id | name       | species       | realm               | ability_count | avg_ability_level |
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+
|           1 | Aurora     | Snow Leopard  | Frostpeak Mountains |             2 |              4.50 |
|           2 | Cinderwing | Dragon        | Emberglow Caverns   |             1 |              8.00 |
|           4 | Nyx        | Shadow Lynx   | Frostpeak Mountains |             1 |              7.00 |
|           3 | Sylphria   | Forest Sprite | Moonpetal Forest    |             1 |              5.00 |
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+

+---------------------+---------------+------------+--------------+
| realm               | magic_density | creature   | species      |
+---------------------+---------------+------------+--------------+
| Emberglow Caverns   |            92 | Cinderwing | Dragon       |
| Frostpeak Mountains |            87 | Aurora     | Snow Leopard |
| Frostpeak Mountains |            87 | Nyx        | Shadow Lynx  |
+---------------------+---------------+------------+--------------+

+------------+---------------+----------------+---------+----------------+---------------------+
| creature   | species       | ability_name   | element | acquired_level | realm               |
+------------+---------------+----------------+---------+----------------+---------------------+
| Aurora     | Snow Leopard  | Frost Aura     | Ice     |              6 | Frostpeak Mountains |
| Aurora     | Snow Leopard  | Veilwalk       | Shadow  |              3 | Frostpeak Mountains |
| Cinderwing | Dragon        | Molten Breath  | Fire    |              8 | Emberglow Caverns   |
| Nyx        | Shadow Lynx   | Starstep Dash  | Storm   |              7 | Frostpeak Mountains |
| Sylphria   | Forest Sprite | Moonlight Heal | Nature  |              5 | Moonpetal Forest    |
+------------+---------------+----------------+---------+----------------+---------------------+


Example Queries:

UNIQUE CREATURE ABILITIES COUNT:
> SELECT
->   a.ability_name,
->   a.element,
->   COUNT(*) AS creatures_with_ability
-> FROM creature_abilities ca
-> JOIN abilities a ON a.ability_id = ca.ability_id
-> GROUP BY a.ability_id
-> ORDER BY creatures_with_ability DESC, a.ability_name;

RESULT:
+----------------+---------+------------------------+
| ability_name   | element | creatures_with_ability |
+----------------+---------+------------------------+
| Frost Aura     | Ice     |                      1 |
| Molten Breath  | Fire    |                      1 |
| Moonlight Heal | Nature  |                      1 |
| Starstep Dash  | Storm   |                      1 |
| Veilwalk       | Shadow  |                      1 |
+----------------+---------+------------------------+

CREATURE PROFILES (realm + ability count):
SELECT
  c.creature_id,
  c.name,
  c.species,
  r.name AS realm,
  COUNT(ca.ability_id) AS ability_count,
  ROUND(AVG(ca.acquired_level), 2) AS avg_ability_level
FROM creatures c
LEFT JOIN realms r ON c.realm_id = r.realm_id
LEFT JOIN creature_abilities ca ON ca.creature_id = c.creature_id
GROUP BY c.creature_id, r.name
ORDER BY ability_count DESC, avg_ability_level DESC;

RESULT:
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+
| creature_id | name       | species       | realm               | ability_count | avg_ability_level |
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+
|           1 | Aurora     | Snow Leopard  | Frostpeak Mountains |             2 |              4.50 |
|           2 | Cinderwing | Dragon        | Emberglow Caverns   |             1 |              8.00 |
|           4 | Nyx        | Shadow Lynx   | Frostpeak Mountains |             1 |              7.00 |
|           3 | Sylphria   | Forest Sprite | Moonpetal Forest    |             1 |              5.00 |
+-------------+------------+---------------+---------------------+---------------+-------------------+

MOST COMMON ABILITIES:
SELECT
  a.ability_name,
  a.element,
  COUNT(*) AS creatures_with_ability
FROM creature_abilities ca
JOIN abilities a ON a.ability_id = ca.ability_id
GROUP BY a.ability_id
ORDER BY creatures_with_ability DESC, a.ability_name;

RESULT:
+----------------+---------+------------------------+
| ability_name   | element | creatures_with_ability |
+----------------+---------+------------------------+
| Frost Aura     | Ice     |                      1 |
| Molten Breath  | Fire    |                      1 |
| Moonlight Heal | Nature  |                      1 |
| Starstep Dash  | Storm   |                      1 |
| Veilwalk       | Shadow  |                      1 |
+----------------+---------+------------------------+

ETC.

---

BACKUP + RESTORE:
Backup + Restore:
Backup
mysqldump -u root -p snow_leopard_codex > snow_leopard_codex.sql

Restore (to a fresh database):
CREATE DATABASE snow_leopard_codex_restore;
mysql -u root -p snow_leopard_codex_restore < snow_leopard_codex.sql


---

Notes on Constraints:
Foreign key constraints enforce relationship integrity (no orphan records)
Junction table uses a composite primary key (creature_id, ability_id)
CHECK constraints ensure values stay in expected ranges

